    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8994" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τρί̄βω</span></b>  (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τείρω</span>), inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τρῑβέμεναι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔτρῑψα</span>,
          inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τρῖψαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">rub</span>, hence
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">thresh</span> corn (by treading out with oxen, see cut),
            <i><span class="en">Il. 20.496</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; μοχλὸν ἐν ὀφθαλμῷ</span>, ‘plunge’ we
          should say (cf. ‘rubbed in’), <i><span class="en">Od.
            9.333</span></i>; pass. and fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wear oneself out</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.735</span></i>. 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
